File: KFC says the 64-year-old phrase doesn't quite suit the current environment in light of the coronavirus pandemic. JOHANNESBURG - It's one of the most recognisable phrases in the world. But fast-food retailer KFC says it’s hitting the pause button on the slogan finger lickin' good. KFC says the 64-year-old phrase doesn't quite suit the current environment in light of the coronavirus pandemic. The move will affect KFC stores around the world. The retailer's not chickening out though and says the finger lickin' good phrase will be back.